Taiwan Offshore Banking Units
Deposits from overseas financial institutions accounted
for $21.65 billion of the total. Nonfinancial organizations
took the remainder of deposits of $1.89 billion.
   Of the overall OBUs, lendings to the financial
institutions constituted $19.59 billion, and the remaining
$3.95 billion were loans to nonfinancial institutions and
investments in financial bills and notes.
   Funds from the Asian region accounted for 84%. Europe
accounted for 8%; North America, 7%; and other areas, 1%.